Form Element - Multiple Related Checkboxes - cml:checkboxes

- Renders a group of checkboxes
- Accepts all Common Attributes

[code]
<cml:checkboxes validates="required" label="Sample checkboxes:">
<cml:checkbox label="Checkbox 1" /> 
<cml:checkbox label="Checkbox 2" /> 
<cml:checkbox label="Checkbox 3" /> 
</cml:checkboxes>
[/code]

<img src="sample_checkboxes.png" />

The [code]<cml:checkbox />[/code] children elements accept the following attributes:

[code]checked[/code]
If this attribute is "true", the child checkbox will be pre-checked when the page loads.

[code]
<cml:checkboxes validates="required" label="Sample checkboxes:"> 
<cml:checkbox label="Checkbox 1" checked="true" /> 
<cml:checkbox label="Checkbox 2" /> 
<cml:checkbox label="Checkbox 3" /> 
</cml:checkboxes>
[/code]

<img src="sample_checkboxes_with_checked.png" />

[code]label[/code]
The visible label for the child checkbox. This is different than the parent [code]<cml:checkboxes>[/code] element's "label" attribute, which is the label for the entire group of checkboxes.

[code]value[/code]
The value that gets submitted if the contributor selects the corresponding child checkbox. If this isn't present, the value of the "label" attribute is submitted.